# Individual: schema1:CaseSeries (CaseSeries)

AnnotationAssertion(schema1:isPartOf schema1:CaseSeries <http://health-lifesci.schema.org>)
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:comment schema1:CaseSeries "A case series (also known as a clinical series) is a medical research study that tracks patients with a known exposure given similar treatment or examines their medical records for exposure and outcome. A case series can be retrospective or prospective and usually involves a smaller number of patients than the more powerful case-control studies or randomized controlled trials. Case series may be consecutive or non-consecutive, depending on whether all cases presenting to the reporting authors over a period of time were included, or only a selection.")
AnnotationAssertion(rdfs:label schema1:CaseSeries "CaseSeries")
ClassAssertion(schema1:MedicalObservationalStudyDesign schema1:CaseSeries)

